#. <section class="sutta" id="sn56.40"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn56.40:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 56"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 56"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.40:0.2"
msgid "4. Sīsapāvanavagga"
msgstr "4. In a Rosewood Forest"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 40. Vādatthikasutta → vādasuttaṃ (bj) | vādino (pts1)
msgctxt "sn56.40:0.3"
msgid "40. Vādatthikasutta"
msgstr "40. Looking For a Debate"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.40:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Yo hi koci, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, take any mendicant who truly understands: ‘This is suffering’ … "
"‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘"
"This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’."

msgctxt "sn56.40:1.2"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, puratthimāya "
"cepi disāya āgaccheyya samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā vādatthiko vādagavesī:"
msgstr ""
"An ascetic or brahmin might come from the east, west, north, or south "
"wanting to debate, seeking a debate, thinking:"

# BB seems to omit sahadhammena
msgctxt "sn56.40:1.3"
msgid ""
"‘vādamassa āropessāmī’ti, taṃ vata sahadhammena saṅkampessati vā "
"sampakampessati vā sampacālessati vāti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"‘I’ll refute their doctrine!’ It’s simply impossible for them to "
"legitimately make that mendicant shake or rock or tremble."

msgctxt "sn56.40:1.4"
msgid "Pacchimāya cepi disāya … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn56.40:1.5"
msgid "uttarāya cepi disāya … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn56.40:1.6"
msgid ""
"dakkhiṇāya cepi disāya āgaccheyya samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā vādatthiko "
"vādagavesī:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn56.40:1.7"
msgid ""
"‘vādamassa āropessāmī’ti, taṃ vata sahadhammena saṅkampessati vā "
"sampakampessati vā sampacālessati vāti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.446"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.40:2.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, silāyūpo soḷasa kukkuko."
msgstr "Suppose there was a stone pillar, sixteen feet long."

msgctxt "sn56.40:2.2"
msgid "Tassassu aṭṭha kukku heṭṭhā nemaṅgamā, aṭṭha kukku uparinemassa."
msgstr "Eight feet were buried underground, and eight above ground."

msgctxt "sn56.40:2.3"
msgid ""
"Puratthimāya cepi disāya āgaccheyya bhusā vātavuṭṭhi, neva saṅkampeyya na "
"sampakampeyya na sampacāleyya; pacchimāya cepi disāya … pe … uttarāya cepi "
"disāya … pe … dakkhiṇāya cepi disāya āgaccheyya bhusā vātavuṭṭhi, neva "
"saṅkampeyya na sampakampeyya na sampacāleyya."
msgstr ""
"Even if violent storms were to blow up out of the east, the west, the north, "
"and the south, they couldn’t make it shake or rock or tremble."

msgctxt "sn56.40:2.4"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "sn56.40:2.5"
msgid "Gambhīrattā, bhikkhave, nemassa sunikhātattā silāyūpassa."
msgstr ""
"It’s because that boundary pillar is firmly embedded, with deep foundations."

msgctxt "sn56.40:2.6"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, yo hi koci bhikkhu ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ "
"pajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti;"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, take any mendicant who truly understands: ‘This is "
"suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of "
"suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’."

msgctxt "sn56.40:2.7"
msgid ""
"puratthimāya cepi disāya āgaccheyya samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā vādatthiko "
"vādagavesī ‘vādamassa āropessāmī’ti, taṃ vata sahadhammena saṅkampessati vā "
"sampakampessati vā sampacālessati vāti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"An ascetic or brahmin might come from the east, west, north, or south "
"wanting to debate, seeking a debate, thinking: ‘I’ll refute their doctrine!’ "
"It’s simply impossible for them to legitimately make that mendicant shake or "
"rock or tremble."

msgctxt "sn56.40:2.8"
msgid "Pacchimāya cepi disāya … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn56.40:2.9"
msgid "uttarāya cepi disāya … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn56.40:2.10"
msgid ""
"dakkhiṇāya cepi disāya āgaccheyya samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā vādatthiko "
"vādagavesī: ‘vādamassa āropessāmī’ti, taṃ vata sahadhammena saṅkampessati vā "
"sampakampessati vā sampacālessati vāti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn56.40:2.11"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "sn56.40:2.12"
msgid "Sudiṭṭhattā, bhikkhave, catunnaṃ ariyasaccānaṃ."
msgstr "It’s because they have clearly seen the four noble truths."

msgctxt "sn56.40:2.13"
msgid "Katamesaṃ catunnaṃ?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "sn56.40:2.14"
msgid ""
"Dukkhassa ariyasaccassa … pe … dukkhanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāya "
"ariyasaccassa."
msgstr "The noble truths of suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the path."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.40:3.1"
msgid ""
"Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yogo karaṇīyo … pe … ‘ayaṃ "
"dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yogo karaṇīyo”ti."
msgstr "That’s why you should practice meditation …”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn56.40:3.2"
msgid "Dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn56.40:3.3"
msgid "Sīsapāvanavaggo catuttho."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.40:4.1"
msgid "Sīsapā khadiro daṇḍo,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn56.40:4.2"
msgid "celā sattisatena ca;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn56.40:4.3"
msgid "Pāṇā sūriyūpamā dvedhā,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn56.40:4.4"
msgid "indakhīlo ca vādinoti."
msgstr ""
